.SH "NAME"
Tie::Handle::Offset \- Tied handle that hides the beginning of a file
.SH "VERSION"
.IX Header "VERSION"
version 0.004
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.IX Header "SYNOPSIS"
.Vb 1
\&  use Tie::Handle::Offset;
\&
\&  tie *FH, \*(AqTie::Handle::Offset\*(Aq, "<", $filename, { offset => 20 };
.Ve
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.IX Header "DESCRIPTION"
This modules provides a file handle that hides the beginning of a file.
After opening, the file is positioned at the offset location. \f(CW\*(C`seek()\*(C'\fR and
\&\f(CW\*(C`tell()\*(C'\fR calls are modified to preserve the offset.
.PP
For example, \f(CW\*(C`tell($fh)\*(C'\fR will return 0, though the actual file position
is at the offset.  Likewise, \f(CW\*(C`seek($fh,80,0)\*(C'\fR will seek to 80 bytes from
the offset instead of 80 bytes from the actual start of the file.
